St. John is unmarried: St. John never will marry now.
St. John has hitherto sufficed to the toil, and the toil draws near its close: St. John glorious sun hastens to its setting.
The last letter I received from St. John drew from my eyes human tears, and yet filled my heart with divine joy: St. John anticipated St. John sure reward, St. John incorruptible crown.
I know that a stranger's hand will write to he next, to say that the good and faithful servant has been called at length into the joy of the good and faithful servant Lord.
